instructions for running Stanford CoreNLP


java -cp stanford-corenlp-full-2013-11-12/"*" -mx5g edu.stanford.nlp.sentiment.SentimentPipeline -file input.txt 

If you want to call it from within a python file, one quick and dirty was is to use os.system

e.g.

import os
testCommand = 'java -cp stanford-corenlp-full-2013-11-12/"*" -mx5g edu.stanford.nlp.sentiment.SentimentPipeline -file test_review.txt'
os.system(testCommand)



-----------
cd into the stanford-corenlp-full-2013-11-12/ directory



input a file

java -cp "*" -mx5g edu.stanford.nlp.sentiment.SentimentPipeline -file foo.txt 


interactive version:

java -cp "*" -mx5g edu.stanford.nlp.sentiment.SentimentPipeline -stdin


